00:20:37,780 --> 00:20:38,520
There's a fire!

275
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:39,620
What? What?

276
00:20:39,620 --> 00:20:41,240
Hey, where's the fire? I don't know.

277
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,200
But the main house...

278
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,400
We have to evacuate our guests!

279
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:44,760
Yes!

280
00:20:51,540 --> 00:20:52,580
Now...

281
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,780
Did you say you are Sakura?

282
00:20:58,300 --> 00:20:59,920
You are...

283
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:06,220
Nao...

284
00:21:11,420 --> 00:21:14,440
You're lying... aren't you?

285
00:21:30,820 --> 00:21:33,220
15 years ago.

286
00:21:34,380 --> 00:21:36,600
What happened in this room?

287
00:21:38,180 --> 00:21:40,500
I wanted to know the truth...

288
00:21:44,780 --> 00:21:47,480
I know my mom didn't kill The Master.

289
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,840
I'm....

290
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:56,200
I'm here to prove my mom's innocence.

291
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:08,100
Did you lie
in front of the hanging scroll?

292
00:22:11,840 --> 00:22:16,900
All of them... All of them...

293
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:19,580
All of them!

294
00:22:24,620 --> 00:22:26,680
Why?

295
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:29,840
Tsubaki.

296
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:35,920
No.

297
00:22:38,180 --> 00:22:40,820
Tsubaki-san, we've got a problem! There's a fire!

298
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:42,760
The whole house is filled with smoke.

299
00:22:42,760 --> 00:22:45,040
Everyone have been evacuated.

300
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:46,720
Except the Grand Master...

301
00:22:46,840 --> 00:22:49,540
His room? Did you check the Grand Master's room?

302
00:22:49,540 --> 00:22:52,600
I can't get close to it
because there's too much smoke.

303
00:22:52,820 --> 00:22:55,080
I'll look for him. Yamaguchi-san,
you take care of the shop.

304
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:55,760
Yes!

305
00:22:56,540 --> 00:22:57,540
Tsubaki!

306
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:01,700
You'd better get out of here quickly.

307
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:04,640
I'll be waiting for you.

308
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:12,020
I'll wait here, for Tsubaki!

309
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,820
Everyone, please calm down.

310
00:23:31,820 --> 00:23:34,140
We're checking the escape routes.

311
00:23:34,860 --> 00:23:35,880
The shop's fine.

312
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:37,460
All right, everybody, this way!

313
00:23:38,380 --> 00:23:40,780
Over here! Where's Tsubaki-san and Nao-san?

314
00:23:41,140 --> 00:23:42,980
What?
Are they still in the main house?

315
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:44,160
Tsubaki-san...?

316
00:23:52,900 --> 00:23:55,480
♪Pinky promise♪

317
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:57,480
♪ If you lie to me♪

318
00:23:57,480 --> 00:24:02,240
♪I'll make you swallow a thousand needles♪

319
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:05,860
♪I cut my finger♪

320
00:24:10,280 --> 00:24:12,280
(Will)

321
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:15,000
♪ I've won♪

322
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:25,520
Grandfather!

323
00:24:25,520 --> 00:24:28,320
Are you there, Grandfather!

324
00:24:31,260 --> 00:24:37,200
Somebody... somebody, please help me.

325
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:41,320
Grandfather...

326
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:51,180
Waiting for Tsubaki.

327
00:24:58,940 --> 00:25:01,340
We can't get there.

328
00:25:01,740 --> 00:25:04,140
It burns my throat.

329
00:25:06,080 --> 00:25:08,620
I can't breathe.

330
00:25:11,380 --> 00:25:13,060
Tsubaki.

331
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:24,980
Tsubaki.

332
00:25:26,820 --> 00:25:28,700
Sakura.

333
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:33,560
Right.

334
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:37,860
You've come to take everything from me.

335
00:25:38,180 --> 00:25:40,360
I've always been afraid

336
00:25:41,040 --> 00:25:42,760
that this day would come.

337
00:25:44,260 --> 00:25:47,920
Tsubaki-san is as good as the Grand Master.

338
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:49,820
He treasures this shop!

339
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:55,640
That was just another lie to deceive me, wasn't it?

340
00:25:56,240 --> 00:26:00,060
To her, I'm the enemy of her parents.

341
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:01,260
But...

342
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:03,600
No problem, we'll take care of it.

343
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:06,800
He loves sweets and he's a purist.

344
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:10,100
We've got two idiots here, so we'll be fine!

345
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:12,040
Why?

346
00:26:12,900 --> 00:26:16,040
You always gave me the words I wanted...

347
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:17,220
Nao.

348
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:28,020
I'm afraid Tsubaki won't forgive me.

349
00:26:28,500 --> 00:26:29,320
But...

350
00:26:29,900 --> 00:26:32,220
Nao, I love you.

351
00:26:33,980 --> 00:26:36,520
Everything about Tsubaki,

352
00:26:37,180 --> 00:26:39,180
I just love them all.

353
00:26:40,940 --> 00:26:45,640
That's all I have to tell him before I lose him.

354
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:58,280
Will you marry me?

355
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:06,660
Nao. Nao.

356
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:10,180
I've found my first...

357
00:27:13,220 --> 00:27:15,000
happiness.

358
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:33,380
Nao-san! What are you doing here?

359
00:27:33,380 --> 00:27:34,160
Let's go!

360
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:36,080
I'll be here.

361
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:37,420
I'm waiting for Tsubaki.

362
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:39,380
We don't know when the fire will get here.

363
00:27:42,040 --> 00:27:43,680
What?

364
00:27:43,940 --> 00:27:44,420
Oh no.

365
00:27:44,420 --> 00:27:45,200
What's wrong with you?

366
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:48,720
Oh no... just that...

367
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:52,840
Wait... quickly...

368
00:27:53,180 --> 00:27:53,980
Nao-san!

369
00:27:53,980 --> 00:27:56,140
Tsubaki.

370
00:27:59,580 --> 00:28:01,940
Nao-san! What's going on?

371
00:28:01,940 --> 00:28:03,760
I don't know. She collapsed suddenly.

372
00:28:03,760 --> 00:28:05,280
Let's get out of here now.

373
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:07,340
No.

374
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:10,820
Wait... no...

375
00:28:16,080 --> 00:28:18,280
(Kougetsuan)
We're all trapped.

376
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:21,560
By the curse of the shop.

377
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:44,120
Nao.

378
00:28:44,780 --> 00:28:45,700
Nao.

379
00:28:47,040 --> 00:28:48,280
Yuko-san.

380
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:51,900
Thank goodness.

381
00:28:51,900 --> 00:28:54,080
You're awake.

382
00:28:55,540 --> 00:28:58,840
Excuse me. This is Hanaoka.
Nao is awake.

383
00:28:58,840 --> 00:29:00,840
Can I get a doctor here, please!

384
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:03,080
I...

385
00:29:03,580 --> 00:29:07,540
I was so shocked to here you were in a fire.

386
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:10,380
But I'm glad that you're safe.

387
00:29:11,160 --> 00:29:12,480
Fire...

388
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:18,060
Tsubaki... Where is Tsubaki?

389
00:29:19,300 --> 00:29:21,300
As for Mr. Tsubaki...

390
00:29:21,940 --> 00:29:23,260
I don't know the details.

391
00:29:23,260 --> 00:29:26,760
- What...
- But with the fire...

392
00:29:26,760 --> 00:29:29,320
I heard that no one died.

393
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:31,380
So I'm sure he's fine.

394
00:29:32,660 --> 00:29:34,300
Thank goodness.

395
00:29:37,540 --> 00:29:38,980
Is Tsubaki awake yet?

396
00:29:41,100 --> 00:29:41,920
Still...

397
00:29:44,420 --> 00:29:46,480
Ugh... it hurts.

398
00:29:46,480 --> 00:29:47,420
Are you OK?

399
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:50,180
What about my baby?

400
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:56,180
Well.

401
00:30:05,580 --> 00:30:08,800
I guess... I didn't make it.

402
00:30:12,540 --> 00:30:14,860
A mom like me...

403
00:30:14,860 --> 00:30:17,920
You must hate me, right?

404
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:21,020
That's not true.

405
00:30:21,620 --> 00:30:22,880
Don't say that!

406
00:30:23,420 --> 00:30:26,100
It was no one's fault!

407
00:30:27,260 --> 00:30:31,320
It was no one's fault. It's okay.

408
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:33,700
I've had my punishment.

409
00:30:37,940 --> 00:30:40,860
Nao-san shouldn't come back to Kougetsuan.

410
00:30:42,260 --> 00:30:45,060
She'll just continue to suffer if she get back.

411
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:48,420
It'll be okay.

412
00:30:49,540 --> 00:30:51,760
Please don't cry.

413
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:55,760
(Kanazawa Daiichi Hospital)

414
00:30:58,100 --> 00:31:00,840
I don't know what I'm supposed to do from now on...

415
00:31:01,800 --> 00:31:04,480
Did Tsubaki get back after that?

416
00:31:05,280 --> 00:31:06,800
Or...

417
00:31:07,500 --> 00:31:09,080
Two days since the fire at Kougetsuan.

418
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:12,680
The locals are mourning the partial loss

419
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:14,280
of the historic main house of the building.

420
00:31:15,100 --> 00:31:17,980
I heard you managed to save the tools,

421
00:31:17,980 --> 00:31:20,700
which are considered municipal cultural assets.

422
00:31:20,840 --> 00:31:22,260
Here it is!

423
00:31:22,260 --> 00:31:24,560
Our young master save this set.

424
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:27,560
Risking his life in the flames,

425
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:31,700
After rescuing the Grand Master,
he went back to get these tools.

426
00:31:35,420 --> 00:31:38,440
The tools which belongs to the proper successor.

427
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:43,640
I wil not let anyone take over this shop.

428
00:31:45,140 --> 00:31:47,640
Tsubaki protected it.

429
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:51,640
I'll be here waiting for Tsubaki!

430
00:31:58,320 --> 00:32:01,620
I've been deceiving Tsubaki all along.

431
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:05,100
Of course he won't forgive me.

432
00:32:12,740 --> 00:32:15,200
Mom...

433
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:17,900
I'm sorry.

434
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:20,240
I couldn't do anything.

435
00:32:21,260 --> 00:32:23,100
Because of that woman...

436
00:32:23,100 --> 00:32:26,100
Even though I figured out that
she was the one who frame you...

437
00:32:29,840 --> 00:32:31,580
I'm sorry...

438
00:32:37,060 --> 00:32:41,120
Sis, are you hungry?

439
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:48,040
Here, you can have one.

440
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:53,280
Thank you.

441
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:55,040
But now...

442
00:32:55,060 --> 00:32:56,260
Go ahead!

443
00:33:23,540 --> 00:33:24,700
Sweet...

444
00:33:28,460 --> 00:33:30,180
Delicious.

445
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:32,880
Delicious.

446
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:34,500
Really?

447
00:33:38,660 --> 00:33:40,520
Thank you.

448
00:33:41,040 --> 00:33:42,320
Haruka!

449
00:33:42,780 --> 00:33:44,780
Mommy!

450
00:33:52,040 --> 00:33:52,980
Nao-chan.

451
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:57,200
Why...

452
00:34:00,740 --> 00:34:03,000
the meal I just ate..

453
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:06,200
was so bland.

454
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:10,940
But these sweets...?

455
00:34:18,080 --> 00:34:18,680
Nao-chan.

456
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:23,060
What do you want to do now?

457
00:34:24,040 --> 00:34:26,000
Do you want to go back to Kougetsuan?

458
00:34:35,140 --> 00:34:37,800
What I really want to do...

459
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:40,440
I...

460
00:34:43,220 --> 00:34:45,420
I just want to make sweets.

461
00:34:47,380 --> 00:34:50,700
I want to go back to that time.

462
00:34:51,220 --> 00:34:53,200
Making sweets was so fun.

463
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:56,700
I'm so happy every time I finish one...

464
00:34:57,520 --> 00:34:59,180
All I have...

465
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:02,380
is just the love for making sweets.

466
00:35:11,920 --> 00:35:13,360
Let's forget everything.

467
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:19,260
Including Kougetsuan...

468
00:35:19,780 --> 00:35:21,000
I love you.

469
00:35:25,260 --> 00:35:26,840
And Tsubaki.

470
00:35:28,580 --> 00:35:32,700
It's all right... I can forget.

471
00:35:33,080 --> 00:35:36,380
I'm sure... I'm sure...

472
00:35:42,380 --> 00:35:44,380
(Kougetsuan)
(Three months later)

473
00:35:46,380 --> 00:35:49,140
And finally, take the sweet paste

474
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:54,500
place it in the centre of the flower
by chopsticks.

475
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:59,000
Now you have the autumn wildflower,
the cosmos.

476
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:01,840
Wow, it's beautiful! It's beautiful!

477
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:04,860
Next month we will be making the peony.

478
00:36:04,860 --> 00:36:06,140
I'll come! Me too!

479
00:36:06,140 --> 00:36:08,040
Me too...

480
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:12,560
What a silly idea, a Japanese sweets class.

481
00:36:12,700 --> 00:36:15,040
As the master of the shop,
this is not your job.

482
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:17,920
What's wrong with trying something new?

483
00:36:18,780 --> 00:36:21,060
And I'm not the master yet.

484
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:24,420
I'm just filling in for the Grand Master
while he's in hospital.

485
00:36:25,900 --> 00:36:27,860
And Nao-san.

486
00:36:28,300 --> 00:36:30,580
When are you going to stop looking for her?

487
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:35,780
I heard you're asking around

488
00:36:35,780 --> 00:36:37,720
all the shop in this prefecture.

489
00:36:39,100 --> 00:36:41,380
What's the point of finding out now?

490
00:36:42,660 --> 00:36:44,020
The day of the fire.

491
00:36:44,780 --> 00:36:46,760
You chose the inheritance

492
00:36:47,100 --> 00:36:49,780
of this shop over her.

493
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:51,780
That was because...

494
00:36:55,540 --> 00:36:57,100
After the fire.

495
00:36:57,820 --> 00:37:00,440
I was unconscious for ten days.

496
00:37:02,020 --> 00:37:03,380
When I woke up,

497
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:06,560
She's gone.

498
00:37:07,740 --> 00:37:10,060
Why do I want to find Nao?

499
00:37:10,700 --> 00:37:12,300
I'm not even sure myself.

500
00:37:13,860 --> 00:37:17,880
I don't know whether this feeling is love or hate.

501
00:37:18,120 --> 00:37:20,160
The one you should be focusing on,

502
00:37:20,900 --> 00:37:22,740
Isn't there anyone else?

503
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,600
(Takatsuki)
Excuse me.

504
00:37:35,040 --> 00:37:37,580
Thanks for holding a class just for me.

505
00:37:38,860 --> 00:37:39,760
No.

506
00:37:52,300 --> 00:37:53,940
Tsubaki-san!

507
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:04,120
Tsubaki-san?

508
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:09,760
Thank goodness!

509
00:38:15,560 --> 00:38:17,240
I'm really sorry.

510
00:38:18,580 --> 00:38:19,560
It's my fault.

511
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:24,080
Please don't apologize anymore.

512
00:38:24,080 --> 00:38:25,920
I did that on my own...

513
00:38:26,620 --> 00:38:28,980
Don't worry about it, really.

514
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:35,860
You picked a very bright red color.

515
00:38:37,200 --> 00:38:40,320
Oh, did I do it wrong?
I'll redo it right away.

516
00:38:42,100 --> 00:38:44,060
Shiori-san, do you like red?

517
00:38:44,500 --> 00:38:46,080
You wear a lot of red kimono too.

518
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:49,840
Ah... yes.

519
00:38:50,320 --> 00:38:51,840
Since I was a kid.

520
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:55,600
It cheers me up
and makes me stand out.

521
00:38:56,560 --> 00:38:57,380
Stand out?

522
00:38:58,180 --> 00:39:00,600
I have two sisters.

523
00:39:01,980 --> 00:39:04,400
They're both beautiful and charming.

524
00:39:05,140 --> 00:39:08,220
Compared to them, I'm so plain and boring.

525
00:39:08,920 --> 00:39:11,820
So if you wear red,

526
00:39:11,820 --> 00:39:14,140
I think people will notice me more.

527
00:39:17,860 --> 00:39:18,760
For my father,

528
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:21,500
he said "Don't wear it, it doesn't suit you".

529
00:39:22,220 --> 00:39:24,300
I'm sure everyone think so.

530
00:39:26,140 --> 00:39:27,780
I don't think...

531
00:39:29,260 --> 00:39:31,060
Why would you assume that?

532
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:32,920
It's my own opinion.

533
00:39:45,260 --> 00:39:47,000
I like it a lot.

534
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:57,060
You can't say that, Tsubaki-san...

535
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:04,580
(Haseya) We're very excited to
become a family with you.

536
00:40:12,040 --> 00:40:15,580
Thank you very much for everything.

537
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:17,880
With my daughter scarred like this,

538
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:20,280
I won't have been surprised if you said no.

539
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:23,520
Oh no... it was an accident.

540
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:24,380
For Shiori-san...

541
00:40:25,140 --> 00:40:28,900
I will make sure she doesn't have to
face any guest, please don't worry.

542
00:40:30,240 --> 00:40:34,020
I'm sorry, this may be old-fashioned, but

543
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:37,100
I'd like Shiori-san to a be homemaker
as much as possible.

544
00:40:40,740 --> 00:40:41,320
Shiori?

545
00:40:43,100 --> 00:40:45,020
Why do you assume?

546
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:47,180
I like it a lot.

547
00:41:10,420 --> 00:41:11,900
Today.

548
00:41:12,340 --> 00:41:16,000
I brought you some cold peonies
as they were in bloom.

549
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:23,940
Excuse me...

550
00:41:23,940 --> 00:41:27,000
Excuse me, has anyone else been here today?

551
00:41:27,120 --> 00:41:29,760
Oh, that wasn't there before.

552
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:31,220
I wonder who did that?

553
00:41:31,440 --> 00:41:32,920
